The paper deals with the problem of maximizing coverage lifetime of a barrier using mobile sensors with limited battery power. This involves optimization of sensor deployment and movement, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of sensors for detection and tracking also suggests the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses energy consumption, which is a topic in networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT).
